Control ttl cache by decorator isn&#39;t support yet. There&#39;s a [feature request](https://github.com/nestjs/nest/pull/2943) in github to include this in a future version.

But, you can use a more verbose approach to deal with it. Inject the cache-manager object into your controllers constructors and use the &#39;wrap&#39; function on each desired route:

```typescript
constructor(
  @Inject(CACHE_MANAGER) private cacheManager
) {}

@Get()
async get(): Promise&lt;any&gt; {
  const customers = await this.cacheManager.wrap(
    &#39;/customers&#39;,
    function() {
      return service.longRunningOperation()
    },
    { ttl: 600 }
  )
  return customers
}
```

